# Project Content Schema

Each project file must describe one WildPointer project.

Example file:

```text
src/content/projects/notes-ai.md
```

Frontmatter:

```yaml
title: "NotesAI"
slug: "notes-ai"
tagline: "AI assistant for personal knowledge and notes"
status: "active"
stage: "development"
stageLabel: "Development"
summary: "NotesAI helps users store, search, and interact with personal notes using natural language."
startedAt: "2026-01-01"

neededRoles:
  - "Backend Developer"
  - "Frontend Developer"
  - "QA Engineer"
  - "Product Lead"

links:
  github: "https://github.com/wildpointerorg/notes-ai"
  docs: "https://github.com/wildpointerorg/notes-ai/docs"
  discussions: "https://github.com/wildpointerorg/notes-ai/discussions"
  roadmap: ""

contacts:
  coordinator: "TBD"
  telegram: ""
  email: ""

featured: true
order: 1
```

Body:

```md
## Project Goal

Describe the problem this project solves.

## Expected Value

Describe the value for users and for the community.

## Current Focus

Describe what the squad is working on now.

## Open Questions

List unresolved questions.
```

---

## Project Field Rules

### title

Human-readable project name.

### slug

URL-safe identifier.

Used for:

```text
/projects/[slug]
```

### status

Allowed values:

```text
active
paused
released
archived
```

### stage

Allowed values:

```text
idea-forming
discovery
product-design
planning
architecture
backlog
development
qa
delivery
operations
feedback
```

### stageLabel

Human-readable stage name.

### summary

Short description for project cards.

Maximum recommended length:

```text
160 characters
```

### startedAt

ISO date.

Example:

```text
2026-01-01
```

### neededRoles

List of roles or contribution types currently needed.

### links

External project resources.

All fields are optional, but keys should exist.

### contacts

Contact information for joining the project.

### featured

Boolean.

Featured projects appear on the home page.

### order

Number used for sorting.

